net.proteusframework.users.model

Class PhoneNumber

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.users.model.PhoneNumber
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, PersonalInformation

    public class PhoneNumber
extends java.lang.Object
implements PersonalInformation, java.io.Serializable
    Encapsulates the information in a phone number. This class is not thread safe.
    Author:
    Russ Tennant (russ@proteus.co)

      • getDataVisibility

        public java.lang.String getDataVisibility()
        Get the data visibility. "Data visibility" is an application specific definition of how contact data may be used. An example use-case would be to define an enum with fields meaning 'internal', 'emergency-only', and 'public-website' and then set this string to one of the enum field names. Type-safety has been intentionally sacrificed for the benefit of providing applications a simple way to store application specific information in way that is searchable and does not require sub-typing value objects. Its strongly recommended that names of enum fields be stored in this String property instead of arbitrary hard-coded string literals.
        Specified by:
        getDataVisibility in interface PersonalInformation
        Returns:
        the data visibility, which won't be null but could be empty string.

      • isNanp

        public boolean isNanp()
        Returns true if the phone number follows the North American Numbering Plan. Phone numbers that follow this plan are generally written (800) 555 - 1111. "800" corresponds to the area code. "555" corresponds to the central office code and "1111" corresponds to the subscriber code.
        Returns:
        Returns the nanp.

      • toExternalForm

        public java.lang.String toExternalForm(@Nullable
                                       java.lang.String ccc)
        Translates this phone number to a String in its external form. The PhoneNumber object can be restored using the valueOf() method.
        Parameters:
        ccc - the country calling code. Optional. The code will only be prepended if it doesn't appear to be included in the number already.
        Returns:
        external form for the phone number.

      • toNANPForm

        public java.lang.String toNANPForm()
        Translates this phone number to a String in nanp form. An example of this form is 123-456-7890. This is used to display a current phone number in a single box entry for a nanp number. This excludes the extension because there is usually a separate entry box for that.
        Returns:
        String. Will be empty string if isNanp() returns false or if any piece of the phone number (area code, central office code, subscriber code) is missing.

      • toURI

        public java.lang.String toURI(java.lang.String scheme,
                              java.lang.String ccc)
        Return the phone number as a URI. Useful for creating telephone links.
        Parameters:

        ccc - the country calling code. Optional. The code will only be prepended if it doesn't appear to be included in the number already.

      • toURI

        public java.lang.String toURI(java.lang.String scheme,
                              @Nullable
                              java.lang.String ccc,
                              @Nullable
                              java.lang.String extensionParameter)
        Return the phone number as a URI. Useful for creating telephone links.
        Parameters:
        scheme - the URI scheme. Usually, "tel". Optional.
        ccc - the country calling code. Optional. The code will only be prepended if it doesn't appear to be included in the number already.
        extensionParameter - extension parameter. One of ";", ";ext=", or ";postd=" are common. Optional. Defaults to ";".
        Returns:
        the URI.

      • valueOf

        public static PhoneNumber valueOf(java.lang.String s)
        Parses a string into a phone number. This method assumes the number follows the North American Numbering Plan and will try to parse it as one.
        Parameters:
        s - The String, may be null.
        Returns:
        PhoneNumber.

      • valueOf

        public static PhoneNumber valueOf(java.lang.String s,
                                  boolean nanp)
        Parses a string into a phone number. This method assumes the number follows the North American Numbering Plan and will try to parse it as a NANP number. Otherwise, it will not attempt to parse it as a NANP number.
        Parameters:
        s - The String, may be null.
        nanp - parse as a North American Number Plan number if the number is 10 digits.
        Returns:
        PhoneNumber.
